Class ClassicSort<X extends Classify<X>>

java.lang.Object
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.sort.helper.GenericSortWithHelper<X>
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.sort.classic.ClassicSort<X>
Type Parameters:
X - the underlying type which must extend Classify.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ProcessingSort<X>, Sort<X>, AutoCloseable
public class ClassicSort<X extends Classify<X>> extends GenericSortWithHelper<X> implements ProcessingSort<X>
This sort method sorts elements according to their class, i.e. the sort key is the value of x.classify().

      public void sort(X[] xs, int from, int to)
      Sorts the specified portion of the array based on the classification of its elements. Elements are grouped into classes defined by their classify() method, and sorted accordingly.
